0.name: Operation Code at Capital One
0.description:
• What we'll do:
You're invited to our Operation Code Meetup, located at and hosted by Capital One in Seattle! Our speakers will be sharing their experiences and career and technical insights that will help give our guests the edge in building their careers.

• Veteran Organizations:
-We'll spotlight our supporting Veteran Service Organizations: FourBlock, USO, The Mission Continues and Travis Manion Foundation, who are helping veterans and serving the community in many different ways.

• Who else will be there?:
-We'll have mentors and guests coming from Capital One, Chef Software, Unity, Stryker, Microsoft, Amazon, Amazon Web Services, Oracle, and many more!

*********************************************

• What's the format of the meetup?
- From 6pm to 6:30pm, we'll eat, drink, and build our connections through informal networking with mentors, developers, entrepreneurs and business leaders.
- 6:30pm to 8pm, we'll hear from our esteemed speakers and guests.
- 8pm to 9pm, an opportunity for guests to build new connections with other guests, mentors, and presenters.

• Who's this for?
- Our meetups are geared towards: software/systems engineers, entrepreneurs, new developers, technical mentors with experience in the tech industry, career mentors with experience in leadership, and those who are interested in expanding their perspectives.
- We are an inclusive community and we invite all veterans and non-veterans to come to share, listen, and learn.
- Those interested in developing careers in tech
- Experienced developers and / or leaders in software industry to share experiences and mentor others.

• What do I need to bring?
- An interest in learning more about the tech industry
- A willingness to connect with others

• Are food and drinks provided?
Yes, Capital One is hosting food and drinks!

1.name: Operation Code's last Meetup for 2018 at...
1.description: This will be the last 2018 Meetup for the year, then we start up again in January 22, 2019!
